.TH "intel_fbc_enable" 9 "intel_fbc_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_fbc_enable \- tries to enable FBC on the CRTC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" intel_fbc_enable
.BI "(struct intel_atomic_state *state "  ","
.BI "struct intel_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
corresponding \fIdrm_crtc_state\fP for \fIcrtc\fP
.IP "crtc" 12
the CRTC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks if the given CRTC was chosen for FBC, then enables it if
possible. Notice that it doesn't activate FBC. It is valid to call
intel_fbc_enable multiple times for the same pipe without an
intel_fbc_disable in the middle, as long as it is deactivated.
